  "body": " Same output in code   The following code compares two more inputs for the same map.  F = np.array([[1, 1, 0], [0, 1, 1]]) u = np.array([0, 1, 2]) v = np.array([1, 0, 3]) d = v - u F @ u, F @ v, d, F @ d  Predict the four code outputs.    The four outputs are [1, 3] , [1, 3] , [1, -1, 1] , and [0, 0] . Thus F @ u and F @ v are the same, and F @ d is [0, 0] .  The equation F @ d = [0, 0] represents The output does not always determine the input uniquely.   "
