  "body": " Two coefficient choices, same predictions   A data matrix stores three measured features for four observations: Observe that the third feature is the sum of the first two features in every row.  Consider the two coefficient vectors In this example, the linear map takes a coefficient vector as input and returns the prediction vector .   Compute .  Compute .  Are the coefficient vectors the same?  Are the predictions the same?  Let . What equations does represent?     We have The coefficient vectors are different, but the predictions are the same.  The difference is The equation , with , represents The vector satisfies these equations. This happens because the third feature repeats information already contained in the first two features: feature 3 equals feature 1 plus feature 2 in every row.   "
