  "title": "Non-uniqueness of the SVD.",
  "body": " Non-uniqueness of the SVD  The SVD is not unique. A matched pair of singular vectors can be multiplied by without changing the product: When a singular value is zero, there can also be many valid choices for the corresponding orthonormal basis vectors. The roles are more important than the specific signs.  "
