  "title": "Unit 6 applied, geometric, and computational interpretation",
  "body": " Unit 6 applied, geometric, and computational interpretation  These solution sketches correspond to the additional applied and computational interpretation exercises at the end of .   Candidate table on a rectangle  The gradient is The interior critical point is and   On , so the boundary critical point is , giving and value .  On , so the boundary critical point is , giving and value .  On , so the boundary critical point is , giving and value .  On , so the boundary critical point is , giving and value .  The corner values are Thus the absolute minimum value is at and the absolute maximum value is at     Parallel gradients on a circle  Use Then The Lagrange equations are   The first two equations say that is parallel to Since the constrained critical points are   The function values are So the absolute maximum is at , and the absolute minimum is at .  Geometrically, points in the direction of fastest increase of , while is perpendicular to the circle. At the maximum and minimum, these directions are parallel or antiparallel.    Quadratic form on the unit circle  For we have On the unit circle,   The maximum value is , attained at The minimum value is , attained at These are the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of : the eigenvalues are and , with eigenvector directions and .    Maximum stretch of a matrix  Since is symmetric, Compute   The eigenvectors have eigenvalues and , respectively. Therefore the singular values are The largest singular value is , so The most-stretched input direction is     Reading an SVD  The nonzero singular values are The matrix has rank Using for positive singular values, and for a null direction,  and   The forgotten input direction is The transmitted input directions are and     Fundamental subspaces from an SVD  Since the rank is , the first two right singular vectors form an orthonormal basis for the row space: The remaining right singular vector gives the null space:   The first two left singular vectors form an orthonormal basis for the column space: Since has two rows and rank ,   The dimensions are and which agrees with rank-nullity for a matrix. Also, and     Energy retained  The squared singular values are The total squared energy is   For , the retained energy is For , the retained energy is Thus the smallest retaining at least of the energy is The rank- reconstruction keeps the directions corresponding to singular values and , and discards the smaller directions corresponding to singular values and .    Code interpretation: rank- reconstruction  The singular values are When , the reconstruction keeps only the singular value . Since is , U[:, :1] has shape , np.diag(s[:1]) has shape , and Vt[:1, :] has shape .  Therefore has shape The rank of is . In this example, so the second input direction is discarded.    Debugging an SVD slice  The wrong slice is Vt[:, :k] . The correct slice is Vt[:k, :] .  For a matrix and , U[:, :1] has shape , np.diag(s[:1]) has shape , and Vt[:, :1] has shape . After the first two factors are multiplied, the result has shape , which cannot be multiplied on the right by another matrix.  The mathematical mistake is that rows of , not columns of , are the transposed right singular vectors used in the reconstruction. The rank- reconstruction must use the first rows of .    Redundant features revisited by singular values  Compute Thus   The third column is the sum of the first two columns, so the columns are dependent. The first two columns are not multiples of each other, so Because has three columns but rank , one singular value is zero.  If , then So different coefficient vectors can give the same output. This is the same nonuniqueness from Unit 2, now detected by a zero singular value.    Low-rank update storage  The product has shape so it can be added to . Since the inner dimension is ,   The full matrix stores numbers. The matrices and together store numbers.  The product is called a low-rank update because the change has rank at most , even though it has the same shape as . This does not mean that has low rank. The update has low rank; the whole updated matrix may still have large rank.   "
